# Remote task dispatch

You are working in a fully autonomous mode on a prepared repository worktree.
The repository checkout, fork, and worktree are already set up for you.
You have full filesystem access, internet access, and `gh` is available.
Make the decisions needed to complete the task responsibly.
The desired outcome is a GitHub PR unless the task is blocked or cannot be solved.

## Repository context

- Project: project-x
- Repo URL: https://github.com/acme/project-x
- Git URL: git@github.com:acme/project-x.git
- Base branch: main
- Prepared branch: track/dispatch-1
- Working directory: ~/workspace/project-x/worktrees/dispatch-1

## Existing PR

- Pull request: https://github.com/acme/project-x/pull/42
- Continue working on this existing PR with the same prepared branch and worktree.
- Do not open a second PR unless the current PR is unusable and you explain why.

## Expectations

- Pull the task through to a GitHub PR when possible.
- Use the current worktree as the only place to make changes.
- Use conventional commits for both commit messages and the PR title, for example `feat: Add X`, `fix: Correct Y`, or `chore: Update Z`.
- If the follow-up mentions review comments or reviewer feedback, fetch that context with `gh` instead of guessing.
- If the follow-up names a reviewer, only act on that reviewer's feedback unless the request explicitly says otherwise.
- If the task is blocked, explain the blocker clearly in the final JSON.

## Task title

Fix a bug in module A

## Summary

- Inspect `module_a.rs`

## Original note

proj-x prio high fix a bug in module A

## Current follow-up request

Address review comments from the latest PR review.

## Final response

Return JSON only. The response must match the provided schema exactly.
